# EmailJS Configuration
# =====================
# Follow these steps to get your credentials:
# 1. Sign up at https://www.emailjs.com/
# 2. Go to Account -> Copy your Public Key
# 3. Go to Email Services -> Create service and copy Service ID
# 4. Go to Email Templates -> Create 3 templates and copy their Template IDs
# 5. Replace the values below with your actual credentials
# 6. Save this file as .env.local in the project root

# EmailJS Service ID (from Email Services page)
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxx

# EmailJS Public Key (from Account page)
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# EmailJS Template IDs (from Email Templates page)
# Template for Contact Form submissions
VITE_EMAILJS_CONTACT_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxx

# Template for Quote Request submissions
VITE_EMAILJS_QUOTE_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxx

# Template for Job Application submissions
VITE_EMAILJS_JOB_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxx

# =====================
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# =====================
# - Do NOT commit .env.local to git (add to .gitignore)
# - Keep your Public Key and Service ID secure
# - Each form type needs its own template
# - Template names must match exactly in EmailJS dashboard
# - Restart dev server after updating .env.local
#
# Example of filled credentials:
# VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_a1b2c3d4e5f6g7h8
# VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=abc123def456ghi789jkl012
# VITE_EMAILJS_CONTACT_TEMPLATE_ID=template_contact_abc123
# VITE_EMAILJS_QUOTE_TEMPLATE_ID=template_quote_def456
# VITE_EMAILJS_JOB_TEMPLATE_ID=template_job_ghi789
